name: Starbucks
directions: Accessible bathroom is straight ahead on the left hand side (with staff room right in front of you and doors to floor on the right). There are 2 more washrooms upstairs (stairs are just to your left when you walk in and washrooms will be on your left in the upstairs area). The code for the upstairs washrooms is 22343.
comment: Never an issue with just having to go in and pee. If you are worried about it you can always sneak upstairs without anyone really noticing :)

name: Fresh on Crawford
directions: There is one "accessible" washroom on the main floor straight through on the right hand side right beside the kitchen before the stairs (I put it in quotations because I'm not sure if the path way to it would really be wide enough for many mobility devices). There are two other single stall washrooms down the stairs (turn left at the bottom).
comment: You have to walk past the cash/hostesses to get to the washrooms but I have never had an issue/they are all pretty cool (and if you tell them you just need to Us he bathroom I doubt anyone would give you any issues)
